Building the API client library requires:
1. Java 1.8+
2. Maven (3.8.3+)/Gradle (7.2+)

## Installation

To install the API client library to your local Maven repository, simply execute:

```shell
mvn clean install
```

To deploy it to a remote Maven repository instead, configure the settings of the repository and execute:

```shell
mvn clean deploy
```

Refer to the [OSSRH Guide](http://central.sonatype.org/pages/ossrh-guide.html) for more information.

### Maven users

Add this dependency to your project's POM:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.openapitools</groupId>
  <artifactId>openapi-java-client</artifactId>
  <version>2.0</version>
  <scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>
```

### Gradle users

Add this dependency to your project's build file:

```groovy
  repositories {
    mavenCentral()     // Needed if the 'openapi-java-client' jar has been published to maven central.
    mavenLocal()       // Needed if the 'openapi-java-client' jar has been published to the local maven repo.
  }

  dependencies {
     implementation "org.openapitools:openapi-java-client:2.0"
  }
```

### Others

At first generate the JAR by executing:

```shell
mvn clean package
```

Then manually install the following JARs:

* `target/openapi-java-client-2.0.jar`
* `target/lib/*.jar`

*SchemaResponsesApi* | [**schemaResponsesRead**](docs/SchemaResponsesApi.md#schemaResponsesRead) | **GET** /schema_responses/{schema_response_id} | Retrieve a Schema Response
*TaxonomiesApi* | [**taxonomiesList**](docs/TaxonomiesApi.md#taxonomiesList) | **GET** /taxonomies/ | List all taxonomies
*TaxonomiesApi* | [**taxonomiesRead**](docs/TaxonomiesApi.md#taxonomiesRead) | **GET** /taxonomies/{taxonomy_id}/ | Retrieve a taxonomy
*UsersApi* | [**usersAddonAccountsList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersAddonAccountsList) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/addons/{provider}/accounts/ | List all addon accounts
*UsersApi* | [**usersAddonAccountsRead**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersAddonAccountsRead) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/addons/{provider}/accounts/{account_id}/ | Retrieve an addon account
*UsersApi* | [**usersAddonsList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersAddonsList) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/addons/ | List all user addons
*UsersApi* | [**usersAddonsRead**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersAddonsRead) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/addons/{provider}/ | Retrieve a user addon
*UsersApi* | [**usersInstitutionsList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersInstitutionsList) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/institutions/ | List all institutions
*UsersApi* | [**usersList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersList) | **GET** /users/ | List all users
*UsersApi* | [**usersNodesList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersNodesList) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/nodes/ | List all nodes
*UsersApi* | [**usersPartialUpdate**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersPartialUpdate) | **PATCH** /users/{user_id}/ | Update a user
*UsersApi* | [**usersPreprintsList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersPreprintsList) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/preprints/ | List all preprints
*UsersApi* | [**usersRead**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersRead) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/ | Retrieve a user
*UsersApi* | [**usersRegistrationsList**](docs/UsersApi.md#usersRegistrationsList) | **GET** /users/{user_id}/registrations/ | List all registrations

## Documentation for Authorization

Endpoints do not require authorization.


## Recommendation

It's recommended to create an instance of `ApiClient` per thread in a multithreaded environment to avoid any potential issues.
